  "prompt": "What talents do Enneagram type 2 people have?",
  "response": "Enneagram Type 2, often referred to as \"The Helper,\" is characterized by a strong desire to be loved and appreciated, often expressed through acts of kindness and service to others. People with this personality type tend to have a natural set of talents and strengths, many of which revolve around their ability to connect with and care for others. Here are some key talents often associated with Enneagram Type 2 individuals:\n\n1. **Empathy and Compassion**  \n   - Type 2s have a natural ability to sense and understand the emotions of others, making them highly empathetic and compassionate. They can easily put themselves in someone else\u2019s shoes and offer genuine support.\n\n2. **Strong Interpersonal Skills**  \n   - They excel at building and maintaining relationships. Their warm, nurturing, and approachable nature makes them exceptional at connecting with people on a deep level.\n\n3. **Service-Oriented Mindset**  \n   - They are often gifted at identifying the needs of others and taking action to meet those needs, whether through emotional support, practical help, or encouragement.\n\n4. **Generosity and Selflessness**  \n   - Type 2s are naturally generous and willing to go out of their way to help others, often without expecting anything in return (though they may seek appreciation).\n\n5. **Conflict Resolution**  \n   - Their ability to understand multiple perspectives and their desire for harmony make them skilled at mediating conflicts and fostering peaceful resolutions.\n\n6. **Emotional Intelligence**  \n   - They are highly attuned to their own emotions and the emotions of others, making them effective at navigating complex social situations and providing emotional guidance.\n\n7. **Encouragement and Motivation**  \n   - Type 2s are often great at lifting others\u2019 spirits, offering encouragement, and motivating people to reach their potential.\n\n8. **Intuitive Listening**  \n   - They have a talent for active listening, making others feel heard and valued. This skill helps them build trust and strong connections.\n\n9. **Creating a Sense of Belonging**  \n   - Type 2s are often skilled at fostering a sense of community and inclusion, making others feel welcomed and appreciated.\n\n10. **Resourcefulness in Helping**  \n   - They are often creative and resourceful when it comes to finding ways to support others, whether through practical solutions, emotional support, or simply being there.\n\nWhile these talents make Enneagram Type 2s invaluable in personal and professional relationships, it\u2019s important for them to also focus on self-care and setting boundaries to avoid burnout or neglecting their own needs.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
